      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"3. INDY MELMEN boasts a strong record this journey with two wins and two minors from four tries. Scored by 7 lengths last time (29.69) in a Grade 7 over 525m at The Meadows. Expected to be in the finish. 2. GNARLACK is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by half a length at this track in a handy 29.71 beating Little Bont. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from four attempts. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. 1. BACK TALK is on a hot streak recording a 29.98 win over 515m at this track last start following on from a fast 24.05 victory at Bendigo over 425m the start prior. This tougher but looks a leading chance again. 4. CORBAN YAXLEY cannot be underestimated.\",\"runners\":[3,2,1,4],\"exclusive\":false}",
